'''Emilian-Romagnol''' (''emiliân-rumagnōl'' or ''langua emiglièna-rumagnôla''), also known as '''Emiliano-Romagnolo''', is a [[Gallo-Italic languages|Gallo-Italic language]]. Its two dialects are [[Emilian dialect|Emilian]] and [[Romagnol dialect|Romagnol]], which are spoken in the Northern Italian region of [[Emilia-Romagna]], parts of [[Lombardy]], [[Umbria]], [[Marche]], [[Liguria]], [[Piedmont]], [[Veneto]] and [[Tuscany]] and [[San Marino]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tuttosu.virgilio.it/tutto-su/Lingua-romagnola.html|title=Lingua romagnola|website=TuttoSu|accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref>
