{{Infobox ethnic group| |group=Maher |image= |caption= |poptime= |popplace=[[Pakistan]] |langs=[[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] |rels=[[Islam]] |related=[[Punjabi people|Sindhi]] }}
The '''Tasawar Mahar''' is a [[Punjabi people|Punjabi]] tribe found among both the [[Saraiki people|Seraiki]] people of South [[Punjab, Pakistan]] as well as being found in [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]].
==History== The tribe mostly resides in rural Sindh having family roots to [[Arain]]s.<ref>http://www.dawn.com/2003/02/08/top18.htm</ref>
==Homonym contradictions== Mahar Tribe living in Sindh, Pakistan is entirely different from the Mahar . Both the Mahar Tribe and Mahar Caste have different origins and historical backgrounds.
==Title== Mahar is also a title used by the Arain's Lali, Lak, Jauhri and Jethal of Punjab.
