==Writing system== Mampruli is written in a [[Latin script|Latin alphabet]], but the [[literacy]] rate is fairly low. The [[orthography]] currently used represents a number of [[allophone|allophonic]] distinctions. There is a description of the process of formulating the orthography.<ref>{{cite book|last=Naden|first=Di / Tony|title=Community involvement in orthography design.|date=2003|publisher=Linguistics Dept., University of Ghana|location=Legon, Ghana|pages=218–221}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Dakubu|first=, M.E. Kropp / E.K.Osam [eds.]|title=Studies in the Languages of the Volta Basin 1|date=2003|publisher=Linguistics Dept., University of Ghana|location=Legon, Ghana}}</ref>
===Alphabet=== {|class="wikitable" |- | a || aa || b || d || e || ɛ || ee || f || g || ' || gb || gy || h || i || k || kp || ky || l || m || n || ny || ŋ || ŋm || o || ɔ || oo || p || r || s || t || u || uu || w || y || z || ’ |}
==Grammar== Mampruli has a fairly conservative Oti-Volta grammatical system. The constituent order in Mampruli sentences is usually [[agent–verb–object]]. There is a simple, non-technical grammatical study <ref>{{cite web|title=A Sketch of Basic Grammar in Mampruli|url=https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/39755804/TN-MP-GrammarU.pdf}}</ref><<to be expanded>>
==Lexicon== The rather unusual trilingual (Mampruli-Spanish-English) dictionary<ref>{{cite book|last=Arana|first=Evangelina, / Mauricio Swadesh|title=Diccionario analitico del mampruli|date=1967|publisher=Museo de las Culturas, , Instituto Nacional de Anthropologia e Historia|location=Mexico D.F.}}</ref> was superseded by the more-reliable simple glossary:<ref>{{cite book|last=Naden|first=Tony [ed.]|title=Mampruli Vocabulary / Ŋmampulli Yɛla|date=1997|publisher=Mamprint (mimeo)|location=Gbeduuri, N.R.}}</ref> a full-featured Mampruli dictionary is in course of preparation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aardvarks Mampruli|url=http://mamprulilex.wordpress.com/}}</ref> A hundred-word sample can be seen on the [[Kamusi project]] site<ref>{{cite web|title=Mampruli|url=http://kamusi.org/languages/mampruli}}</ref>
